        "action": "British STANDARD Time",
        "additional_details": "I propose that the clocks go forward to BST  'summer time' and then stays there e.g. no more back and forth every year. It would bring the winter daylight hours closer to the regular working day.\r\n\r\nThis would save industry, business and individual households, money, resources and the effort of having to go to each watch, clock and timepiece every six months.",
